# AirShop Positioning

- AirShop is category agnostic. Do not frame it as only for "shops."
- Prefer "business" or "businesses" as the default wording.
- Use category-specific examples only as examples, not as the product definition.
- Favor examples already reflected on the landing page, such as CNC businesses, custom fabricators, rental companies, manufacturers, cabinet makers, and event planners.
- When writing acquisition content, keep the core positioning broad while using targeted use cases to attract relevant audiences.
- Keep CTA panel titles short and punchy. Avoid long headings that wrap awkwardly.
- Use sentence case for article titles and CTA titles.
- Capitalize the first word and proper nouns, not every major word.
- Avoid old-school title case unless there is a specific brand or stylistic reason.
- Do not apply sentence case mechanically. Prioritize wording that sounds natural, modern, and editorial.
- Avoid flattening strong phrasing into generic or awkward copy just to satisfy a capitalization rule.
